<section class="flex space-x-2 items-start">
  <div>
    <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-bold tracking-tight leading-none text-gray-900 lg:mb-6 md:text-3xl xl:text-4xl dark:text-white">
      Next Steps:
    </h2>
    <ol class="max-w-md space-y-1 text-gray-500 list-decimal list-inside dark:text-gray-400">
      <li>
        You will receive an email on <span class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white"><%= @customer.email %></span> with instructions on the next steps to finalize the creation of your admin/owner account.
      </li>
      <li>
        Once your admin/owner account created and confirm you can login and depending on your plan invite other users to assist you in creating or managing events.
      </li>
    </ol>
  </div>
  <div>
    <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-bold tracking-tight leading-none text-gray-900 lg:mb-6 md:text-3xl xl:text-4xl dark:text-white">
      FAQ
    </h2>
    <ul class="max-w-md space-y-1 text-gray-500 list-disc list-inside dark:text-gray-400">
      <li>
        <span class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">What is your email address?</span><br/>
        You will receive an email from no-reply@thepew.io
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Didn't receive the email:</span><br/>
        Before reaching out to our support team, make sure you didn't delete our email or that it didn't land into your spam folder.
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">The invitation has expired</span><br/>
        For your safety the link to create your admin/owner account has a limited lifetime. Should you not be able to use this link before it expires, please reach out to our support team.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div>
    <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-bold tracking-tight leading-none text-gray-900 lg:mb-6 md:text-3xl xl:text-4xl dark:text-white">
      Meanwhile:
    </h2>
    <ol class="max-w-md space-y-1 text-gray-500 list-decimal list-inside dark:text-gray-400">
      <li>
        You can read our documentation at
      </li>
      <li>
        You can join the conversation on discourse
      </li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>
